## AI Development Governance

This project is equipped with comprehensive AI development workflow governance, generated by [bbg](https://github.com/nicepkg/bbg). When you open this project with any supported AI coding tool, you get a consistent, high-quality development workflow.

### Supported AI Tools

| Tool | Config Directory | Description |
|------|-----------------|-------------|
| Claude Code | `.claude/` | Settings, slash commands |
| OpenCode | `.opencode/` | Instructions, commands |
| Cursor | `.cursor/rules/` | Rule files (.mdc) |
| Codex CLI | `.codex/` | Config, AGENTS.md |
| Gemini | `.gemini/` | Settings, reusable prompts |

### Model Selection

bbg does not pin a required model for any AI tool. It manages workflow entrypoints, runtime context, review gates, and role/capability guidance.

Choose any supported model in your current tool that matches the work:

- planner work: strong reasoning and architecture analysis
- implementer work: strong code editing and iterative verification
- reviewer work: strong code review and risk detection

If your tool supports switching models directly, keep using the tool and change the model there instead of changing bbg-generated files.

### Governance Resources

| Directory | Contents |
|-----------|----------|
| `agents/` | Agent definitions for specialized AI tasks |
| `skills/` | Detailed workflow instructions (SKILL.md per skill) |
| `rules/` | Coding rules organized by language |
| `commands/` | Slash commands for AI tools |
| `hooks/` | Automation hooks for session lifecycle |
| `contexts/` | Operational modes (dev, review, research) |
| `mcp-configs/` | MCP server configurations |

### Primary Entrypoints

- **Analyze**: `bbg analyze` -- Build or refresh project and workspace understanding
- **Start**: `bbg start "<task>"` -- Begin a task using the primary workflow entrypoint
- **Resume**: `bbg resume <task-id>` -- Continue an existing prepared task session
- **Status**: `bbg status` -- Inspect analyze and task session state
- **Add Repo**: `bbg add-repo <path-or-url>` -- Register a new repository and analyze it by default

### Harness + Hermes

- **Harness** keeps execution quality consistent across Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Gemini, and OpenCode
- **Hermes** captures reusable learnings through query, distill, draft, verify, and promote flows
- Use `bbg analyze` before implementation on first adoption or after major repo changes
- Use `bbg start "<task>"` as the default implementation entrypoint
- Common Hermes entry points: `bbg hermes query`, `bbg hermes distill`, `bbg hermes draft-skill`, `bbg hermes draft-rule`, `bbg hermes verify`, `bbg hermes promote`

Practical harness-engineering helpers:

- `bbg task-env start "<task>"` for isolated git worktrees and per-task artifact directories
- `bbg observe start "<topic>"` for UI, log, metric, and trace capture
- `bbg doc-garden` for stale-reference scans across repo docs
- `bbg loop-start` and `bbg loop-status` for long-running verification loops

